/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-ce23f0e\" data-id=\"ce23f0e\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-040d902 elementor-position-top elementor-widget elementor-widget-image-box\" data-id=\"040d902\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image-box.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-image-box-wrapper\"><figure class=\"elementor-image-box-img\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"167\" src=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/bee-300x167-2.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-image-3407\" alt=\"\" \/><\/figure><div class=\"elementor-image-box-content\"><h5 class=\"elementor-image-box-title\">BEE<\/h5><\/div><\/div>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7f92dd0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer\" data-id=\"7f92dd0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"spacer.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer-inner\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bac5d74 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"bac5d74\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Wasps, hornets and bees are not only nuisance pests but can potentially become a serious danger for humans. These insects cause stress and fear whenever they appear and the best way to avoid this unpleasant occurrence is to order a\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/contact-acme-pest-control-milton\/\">professional wasp nest removal on time<\/a>; as well as hornet nest removal or bee nest removal.<\/p><p>If you are not very knowledgeable of wasps, bees and hornets, you may not be able to see the difference between these pests. However, if you pay attention, you will notice that they only look so similar from a distance. There are many types of bees but generally, bees are smaller in size than wasps and hornets; they are easily recognizable by their yellow and black stripes and tiny hair all over their bodies. Wasps, on the other hand, are also black and yellow but they are not fuzzy and they are larger than carpenter bees. Lastly, hornets are larger than wasps and are also not fuzzy; they can be black and white or reddish-brown.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-97e5f49 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"97e5f49\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">FACTS<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6750400 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"6750400\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \"><div class=\"wpb_wrapper\"><div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \"><div class=\"wpb_wrapper\"><ul><li>Bees, wasps and hornets inject a venom into the victim\u2019s skin through the stinger<\/li><li>If you come close to a wasp nest or hornet nest, you may get attacked several times as these insects have stingers without barbs<\/li><li>Bee, on the other hand, has a barbed stinger. Once a bee stings a victim, the barbed stinger will remain in the victim\u2019s skin with the released venom. When the stinger breaks off, the bee will die, which means that bees sting only if they feel seriously threatened<\/li><li>One of the major dangers followed by stings of wasps, bees and hornets is the potential allergic reaction<\/li><li>Around 3% of people have allergic reactions to stings of wasps and bees while 0.8% of victims stung by bees experience anaphylaxis, a life-threatening allergic reaction<\/li><li>The most common reaction to a bee sting is a painful, reddened skin at the attacked area, followed by itching and\/or swelling<\/li><li>This reaction usually disappears within a few hours, leaving no further consequences. In case of a large local reaction, the mentioned effects could last for around a week<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1a53a5a elementor-align-center elementor-widget elementor-widget-global elementor-global-4670 elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"1a53a5a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-lg\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/appointment\/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Book An Appointment<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0c5284b elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer\" data-id=\"0c5284b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"spacer.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer-inner\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t